ctive","usage":"tip(1x), top(1x)"},"G283":{"id":"G283","lemma":"ἀμίαντος","translit":"amíantos","derivation":"from G1 (Α) (as a negative particle) and a derivative of G3392 (μιαίνω);","strongs_def":"unsoiled, i.e. (figuratively) pure","kjv_def":"undefiled","pos":"adjective","usage":"undefiled(4x)"},"G258":{"id":"G258","lemma":"ἀλώπηξ","translit":"alṓpēx","derivation":"of uncertain derivation;","strongs_def":"a fox, i.e. (figuratively) a cunning person","kjv_def":"fox","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"fox(3x)"},"G228":{"id":"G228","lemma":"ἀληθινός","translit":"alēthinós","derivation":"from G227 (ἀληθής);","strongs_def":"truthful","kjv_def":"true","pos":"adjective","usage":"true(27x)"},"G243":{"id":"G243","lemma":"ἄλλος","translit":"állos","derivation":"a primary word;","strongs_def":"\"else,\" i.e. different (in many applications)","kjv_def":"more, one (another), (an-, some an-)other(-s, -wise)","pos":"adjective","usage":"another(62x), some(11x), one(4x)"},"G281":{"id":"G281","lemma":"ἀμήν","translit":"amḗn","derivation":"of Hebrew origin (H0543);","strongs_def":"properly, firm, i.e. (figuratively) trustworthy; adverbially, surely (often as interjection, so be it)","kjv_def":"amen, verily","pos":"particle indeclinable","usage":"verily(101x), amen(51x)"},"G225":{"id":"G225","lemma":"ἀλήθεια","translit":"alḗtheia","derivation":"from G227 (ἀληθής);","strongs_def":"truth","kjv_def":"true, X truly, truth, verity","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"truth(107x), true(1x), verity(1x)"},"G226":{"id":"G226","lemma":"ἀληθεύω","translit":"alētheúō","derivation":"from G227 (ἀληθής);","strongs_def":"to be true (in doctrine and profession)","kjv_def":"speak (tell) the truth","pos":"verb"},"G299":{"id":"G299","lemma":"ἄμωμος","translit":"ámōmos","derivation":"from G1 (Α) (as a negative particle) and G3470 (μῶμος);","strongs_def":"unblemished (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"without blame (blemish, fault, spot), faultless, unblamable","pos":"adjective","usage":"unblameable(1x), fau