ρ);","strongs_def":"man-defender; Alexander, the name of three Israelites and one other man","kjv_def":"Alexander","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Alexander(6x)"},"G229":{"id":"G229","lemma":"ἀλήθω","translit":"alḗthō","derivation":"from the same as G224 (ἄλευρον);","strongs_def":"to grind","kjv_def":"grind","pos":"verb","usage":"grinding(2x)"},"G286":{"id":"G286","lemma":"ἀμνός","translit":"amnós","derivation":"apparently a primary word;","strongs_def":"a lamb","kjv_def":"lamb","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"lamb(4x)"},"G230":{"id":"G230","lemma":"ἀληθῶς","translit":"alēthōs","derivation":"adverb from G227 (ἀληθής);","strongs_def":"truly","kjv_def":"indeed, surely, of a surety, truly, of a (in) truth, verily, very","pos":"adverb","usage":"indeed(6x), surely(3x), truly(2x), very(1x)"},"G291":{"id":"G291","lemma":"Ἀμπλίας","translit":"Amplías","derivation":"contracted for Latin ampliatus (enlarged);","strongs_def":"Amplias, a Roman Christian","kjv_def":"Amplias","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Amplias(1x)"},"G238":{"id":"G238","lemma":"ἀλληγορέω","translit":"allēgoréō","derivation":"from G243 (ἄλλος) and (to harangue (compare G58 (ἀγορά)));","strongs_def":"to allegorize","kjv_def":"be an allegory (the Greek word itself)","pos":"verb"},"G250":{"id":"G250","lemma":"ἀλόη","translit":"alóē","derivation":"of foreign origin (compare G174 (ἀκάνθινος));","strongs_def":"aloes (the gum)","kjv_def":"aloes","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"aloes(1x)"},"G265":{"id":"G265","lemma":"ἁμάρτημα","translit":"hamártēma","derivation":"from G264 (ἁμαρτάνω);","strongs_def":"a sin (properly concrete)","kjv_def":"sin","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"sin(4x)"},"G235":{"id":"G235","lemma":"ἀλλά","translit":"allá","derivation":"neuter plural of G243 (ἄλλος);","strongs_def":"properly, other things, i.e. (adverbially) contrariwise (in many relations)","kjv_def":"and, but (even), howbeit, indeed, nay, nevertheless, no, notwithstanding, save, therefore, yea, yet","pos":"conjunction","usag